Pre-Game Insights: Australia and England have played 23 T20Is with Australia winning 10 occasions and England winning 11.
Australia won their tournament opener against Oman, while England's opener against Scotland was washed out.
Mitchell Marsh will lead Australia, while Jos Buttler and Phil Salt are crucial for England's quick starts.
The pitch has provided assistance to both fast bowlers and spinners, with an average first innings score of 151.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is the 23rd meeting between Australia and England in T20Is.
The Kensington Oval pitch in Barbados is known for assisting both bowlers and batters.
